1
00:00:03,254 --> 00:00:05,507
<i>Within the spreading darkness</i>

2
00:00:05,590 --> 00:00:08,218
<i>I pledged a vow to the revolution</i>

3
00:00:08,384 --> 00:00:13,389
<i>I can't let anybody interrupt it</i>

4
00:00:13,473 --> 00:00:18,561
<i>I'm going to change</i>

5
00:00:27,028 --> 00:00:31,282
<i>The future that
the forbidden fruit foretells...</i>

6
00:00:31,366 --> 00:00:35,411
<i>I'm going to change</i>

7
00:00:35,495 --> 00:00:39,749
<i>The dream into reality</i>

8
00:00:42,335 --> 00:00:48,466
<i>The ending</i>

9
00:00:48,550 --> 00:00:51,594
<i>That everybody wants</i>

10
00:00:52,595 --> 00:00:54,847
<i>Within the spreading darkness</i>

11
00:00:54,931 --> 00:00:57,642
<i>I pledged our vow to the revolution</i>

12
00:00:57,725 --> 00:01:02,522
<i>I can't let anybody interrupt it</i>

13
00:01:02,689 --> 00:01:07,902
<i>Someday I'll show you</i>

14
00:01:07,986 --> 00:01:11,406
<i>A bright and ideal</i>

15
00:01:11,489 --> 00:01:17,287
<i>World</i>

16
00:01:27,422 --> 00:01:30,466
Matsuda! This isn't child's play.
Don't joke around.

17
00:01:30,675 --> 00:01:31,676
Okay. . -

18
00:01:32,635 --> 00:01:34,929
This is the Kira case!
Take it seriously!

19
00:01:35,013 --> 00:01:36,055
Sorry.

20
00:01:36,848 --> 00:01:38,933
Matsuda!
I mean, Mr. Matsuda, please stop.

21
00:01:39,017 --> 00:01:40,101
Matsuda. . .?

22
00:01:40,226 --> 00:01:41,936
I don't want to be dead weight.

23
00:01:42,854 --> 00:01:44,022
Ryuzaki!

24
00:01:44,314 --> 00:01:47,942
Is there anything I can do
besides being a manager?

25
00:01:48,067 --> 00:01:50,069
Could you get me
another cup of coffee?

26
00:01:50,403 --> 00:01:51,446
What?

27
00:01:54,365 --> 00:01:58,286
I want to play a more active role!

28
00:01:58,286 --> 00:01:59,746
I WANT TO PLAY A MORE
ACTIVE ROLE!

29
00:01:59,829 --> 00:02:02,832
MATS U DA

30
00:02:04,626 --> 00:02:05,668
I love you.

31
00:02:07,420 --> 00:02:08,546
So please...

32
00:02:09,130 --> 00:02:10,673
don't say you're going home.

33
00:02:12,008 --> 00:02:14,260
Stay by my side, forever...

34
00:02:15,928 --> 00:02:17,305
Oh! Mr. Director...

35
00:02:17,388 --> 00:02:20,475
I have a boyfriend.
Can we cut the love scenes please?

36
00:02:20,975 --> 00:02:22,018
Wait a second!

37
00:02:22,268 --> 00:02:23,686
Where is this coming from?!

38
00:02:23,770 --> 00:02:25,438
Can't we fake a kiss?

39
00:02:26,356 --> 00:02:28,858
We can't make a movie like that!

40
00:02:28,941 --> 00:02:30,109
If I say no, then it's no!

41
00:02:37,700 --> 00:02:39,661
<i>Yotsuba Group's Tokyo head office...</i>

42
00:02:41,245 --> 00:02:42,622
<i>Today is Friday.</i>

43
00:02:44,457 --> 00:02:48,211
<i>Deaths that are beneficial to Yotsuba
are concentrated around the weekend.</i>

44
00:02:50,755 --> 00:02:52,632
<i>I don't want to be dead weight here.</i>

45
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:55,259
<i>Mr. Mogi's been amazing
since the beginning.</i>

46
00:02:55,635 --> 00:02:57,637
<i>Matsuda! This isn't child's play!</i>

47
00:02:57,720 --> 00:02:58,888
<i>Take it seriously!</i>

48
00:02:58,971 --> 00:03:00,640
<i>Matsuda is a natural at that.</i>

49
00:03:00,723 --> 00:03:02,183
<i>Could you get me
another cup of coffee?</i>

50
00:03:02,350 --> 00:03:03,476
<i>Matsuda!</i>

51
00:03:10,858 --> 00:03:12,360
NISHINAKA GROUP

52
00:03:12,819 --> 00:03:14,153
Hey, Matsu!

53
00:03:14,612 --> 00:03:15,947
He went off somewhere.

54
00:03:16,447 --> 00:03:17,573
Huh?!

55
00:03:37,343 --> 00:03:38,511
So...

56
00:03:38,720 --> 00:03:40,346
Please check this list.

57
00:03:40,847 --> 00:03:41,931
Understood.

58
00:03:43,558 --> 00:03:47,895
<i>Would Ipunish evil-doers
if I could kill</i>

59
00:03:48,521 --> 00:03:50,606
<i>just by seeing
someone's face and name?</i>

60
00:03:51,107 --> 00:03:54,819
<i>Indeed, there are people that
the world can do without...</i>

61
00:03:55,361 --> 00:03:57,655
<i>But I don't think that
I would become a murderer...</i>

62
00:03:57,739 --> 00:04:00,867
<i>just to change the world...</i>

63
00:04:02,577 --> 00:04:03,870
<i>I'm thinking too hard about this.</i>

64
00:04:04,454 --> 00:04:06,080
<i>There's no way that anyone
could murder so many people...</i>

65
00:04:06,164 --> 00:04:07,707
<i>- and not have any memories of doing so.
- What's wrong'?</i>

66
00:04:09,041 --> 00:04:10,918
You're staring at me...

67
00:04:11,419 --> 00:04:15,256
You're angry that I'm
the only one eating cake, aren't you?

68
00:04:15,590 --> 00:04:17,133
No, that's not it...

69
00:04:17,216 --> 00:04:19,343
- Here.
- I wasn't envying you.

70
00:04:20,219 --> 00:04:21,262
<i>Ryuzaki.</i>

71
00:04:21,429 --> 00:04:22,472
What is it, Watari?

72
00:04:23,181 --> 00:04:27,769
<i>Detective Era/do Coil has been
asked to uncover L's identity.</i>

73
00:04:29,228 --> 00:04:33,858
Isn't Eraldo Coil the man who's
the next greatest detective after L?

74
00:04:34,484 --> 00:04:36,110
Who in the world would
send such a request?

75
00:04:37,487 --> 00:04:40,490
<i>The person who requested it is the V.P.
of the rights and planning department</i>

76
00:04:40,573 --> 00:04:41,991
<i>of Yotsuba Group's main office,</i>

77
00:04:42,074 --> 00:04:44,160
<i>ll/lasah/ko Maia.</i>

78
00:04:44,619 --> 00:04:46,162
So it was Yotsuba!

79
00:04:46,704 --> 00:04:48,706
Yotsuba is linked to Kira.

80
00:04:49,332 --> 00:04:51,667
If they want L's identity,

81
00:04:52,210 --> 00:04:54,086
then that means they
probably want to kill him.

82
00:04:54,712 --> 00:04:56,088
That's not good.

83
00:04:56,214 --> 00:05:00,218
We're already shorthanded,
and now we have to worry about Coil too?

84
00:05:01,135 --> 00:05:05,890
It's all right. The detective known
as Eraldo Coil is me.

85
00:05:07,517 --> 00:05:12,355
The three top detectives in the world,
L, Coil, and Deneuve...

86
00:05:12,772 --> 00:05:14,023
are all me.

87
00:05:14,565 --> 00:05:17,944
People who are trying to uncover me
usually fall for this.

88
00:05:20,238 --> 00:05:23,032
I'll give you a strawberry,
so please keep it a secret.

89
00:05:24,450 --> 00:05:26,160
As I expected of you, Ryuzaki.

90
00:05:41,425 --> 00:05:43,719
<i>Maybe I should leave
while I have a chance.</i>

91
00:05:43,928 --> 00:05:46,013
<i>No, then there would have been
no point in coming here.</i>

92
00:05:46,764 --> 00:05:49,767
<i>Should I wait until evelyone's gone
and search the offices?</i>

93
00:05:50,101 --> 00:05:52,311
<i>No, if I were caught doing that...</i>

94
00:05:53,271 --> 00:05:54,772
<i>It's probably better if I leave...</i>

95
00:05:56,274 --> 00:05:57,483
Not that again.

96
00:05:57,984 --> 00:05:59,151
I'm exhausted...

97
00:05:59,610 --> 00:06:01,612
At least it's before the weekend.

98
00:06:02,405 --> 00:06:04,740
We don't know how long
these secret meetings last.

99
00:06:04,991 --> 00:06:07,618
If these were on a Monday, I'd get
depressed about coming to the office.

100
00:06:08,786 --> 00:06:11,080
<i>Secret meetings? All right!</i>

101
00:06:20,298 --> 00:06:21,340
<i>The nineteenth floor!</i>

102
00:06:24,135 --> 00:06:25,177
<i>I've come this far!</i>

103
00:06:26,304 --> 00:06:27,388
<i>I'm going to do this!</i>

104
00:06:28,973 --> 00:06:31,726
Okay. I just have to get
close to him, right?

105
00:06:32,435 --> 00:06:33,436
Leave it to me.

106
00:06:33,978 --> 00:06:37,857
I just have to make it possible to get
around the security cameras and systems

107
00:06:37,940 --> 00:06:41,986
at the Yotsuba Tokyo main offices,
where this guy works, right?

108
00:06:42,653 --> 00:06:47,658
Yes... It is safe to assume that
Kira and Yotsuba are connected.

109
00:06:48,492 --> 00:06:50,077
We're going to check Yotsuba

110
00:06:50,453 --> 00:06:54,415
to see who and how many
have the power.

111
00:06:54,498 --> 00:06:56,417
It is important that we gain
a clear understanding quickly.

112
00:07:20,858 --> 00:07:22,735
We must not allow Yotsuba to

113
00:07:22,818 --> 00:07:24,946
figure out that we are
investigating them.

114
00:07:25,529 --> 00:07:29,533
If someone notices, please assume that
we'll no longer be able to catch Kira.

115
00:07:31,369 --> 00:07:33,746
<i>Damn it. I can't hear them clearly.</i>

116
00:07:34,246 --> 00:07:37,416
<i>If I could only hear one thing,
something important...</i>

117
00:07:42,004 --> 00:07:43,381
Rather, he's in the way.

118
00:07:43,464 --> 00:07:45,049
Let's kill him and split up his stocks.

119
00:07:45,299 --> 00:07:47,051
<i>I just heard them say, "kill"!</i>

120
00:07:49,053 --> 00:07:50,221
Damn it, Kira sure is...

121
00:07:50,346 --> 00:07:53,641
<i>Kira! There it is! Kira!
There it is! What?!</i>

122
00:07:53,808 --> 00:07:56,560
<i>"Let's have Kira kill him"?
I heard it!</i>

123
00:07:56,852 --> 00:07:58,604
<i>They're really working with Kira...</i>

124
00:07:59,146 --> 00:08:01,107
<i>I did it... I did a great job!</i>

125
00:08:10,616 --> 00:08:11,784
Who are you?!

126
00:08:13,452 --> 00:08:16,580
Please be sure not to act
out of panic or haste.

127
00:08:17,164 --> 00:08:19,125
And don't take matters
into your own hands.

128
00:08:20,084 --> 00:08:21,085
<i>Ryuzaki...</i>

129
00:08:21,502 --> 00:08:22,670
What is it, Watari?

130
00:08:23,129 --> 00:08:26,590
<i>Matsuda has sent
an emergency signal from his belt...</i>

131
00:08:27,675 --> 00:08:28,718
From where?

132
00:08:29,218 --> 00:08:33,639
Well, it seems it's coming from within
Yotsuba Tokyo's main offices.

133
00:08:34,515 --> 00:08:39,562
My name is Taro Matsui.
An agent with Yoshida Productions!

134
00:08:39,895 --> 00:08:43,107
How would you like to use
our top multi-talented star, Misa Amane,

135
00:08:43,190 --> 00:08:47,695
as the new spokeswoman for
your company and for your commercials?!

136
00:08:49,155 --> 00:08:51,240
Forget about everything I just said.

137
00:08:52,366 --> 00:08:53,826
We'll need to rethink our strategy.

138
00:08:56,078 --> 00:08:57,538
Matsuda, you idiot!

139
00:09:11,260 --> 00:09:12,845
Yoshida Productions...

140
00:09:13,179 --> 00:09:14,305
Taro Matsui...

141
00:09:16,599 --> 00:09:18,142
He doesn't have anything
suspicious on him.

142
00:09:19,101 --> 00:09:20,853
And he doesn't seem to
be a corporate spy.

143
00:09:21,520 --> 00:09:23,397
Yes, well, please...

144
00:09:23,481 --> 00:09:26,233
Please take Misa-Misa
into consideration.

145
00:09:29,528 --> 00:09:30,780
<i>These two are only lookouts...</i>

146
00:09:31,363 --> 00:09:34,825
<i>The rest of them must be talking about
how to dispose of me.</i>

147
00:09:35,326 --> 00:09:36,786
<i>Am I going to be killed?</i>

148
00:09:37,828 --> 00:09:39,872
<i>I wonder if the emergency signal
was received...</i>

149
00:09:40,206 --> 00:09:43,459
<i>Anyway, I wonder if
Ryuzaki will save me.</i>

150
00:09:44,168 --> 00:09:46,170
<i>What's gonna happen to me?</i>

151
00:09:50,549 --> 00:09:53,928
You can answer it.
Don't say that you're here.

152
00:09:54,845 --> 00:09:58,599
Hold it away from your ear,
so we can hear.

153
00:09:59,308 --> 00:10:00,434
Okay. . -

154
00:10:02,686 --> 00:10:03,687
Hello?

155
00:10:04,188 --> 00:10:05,439
<i>Hey, Matsui!</i>

156
00:10:07,274 --> 00:10:08,400
<i>Ryuzaki!</i>

157
00:10:10,361 --> 00:10:13,280
<i>It's me. . .Asahi.
Been a while!</i>

158
00:10:13,364 --> 00:10:15,533
Oh... Asahi, it's been a while.

159
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:19,078
You don't sound like you're out.
You home already?

160
00:10:19,703 --> 00:10:20,746
<i>Yeah...</i>

161
00:10:21,163 --> 00:10:22,456
Are you by yourself?

162
00:10:22,873 --> 00:10:25,543
Yeah... I'm by myself.
What's up?

163
00:10:26,127 --> 00:10:28,879
Misa Amane is somewhere else.
Matsuda is alone.

164
00:10:30,798 --> 00:10:32,383
Wanna go drinking?

165
00:10:33,175 --> 00:10:37,138
<i>What? Now?
Sorry, I'm gonna have to pass...</i>

166
00:10:37,471 --> 00:10:38,722
What the hell?

167
00:10:38,806 --> 00:10:41,225
Don't tell me you're going through
money troubles again?

168
00:10:41,475 --> 00:10:42,476
<i>"Troubles?"</i>

169
00:10:43,060 --> 00:10:47,356
Yeah, my finances are totally
in trouble. That's obvious.

170
00:10:48,649 --> 00:10:50,359
Matsuda's totally in trouble.

171
00:10:50,776 --> 00:10:51,819
Oh well.

172
00:10:52,361 --> 00:10:54,738
<i>I'll ask you out again
some other time. Later...</i>

173
00:11:01,453 --> 00:11:04,415
So what do you think
about Misa-Misa?

174
00:11:04,707 --> 00:11:07,042
I think she'll be great
for your company.

175
00:11:09,545 --> 00:11:12,715
If you're going to pitch someone,
shouldn't you bring them with you?

176
00:11:14,717 --> 00:11:16,886
Are you really her manager?

177
00:11:17,887 --> 00:11:20,806
Well, right now she's filming
a movie nearby.

178
00:11:21,015 --> 00:11:23,392
I'll call her here once she's finished.

179
00:11:23,475 --> 00:11:25,728
Please make her the spokeswoman
of your company!

180
00:11:26,228 --> 00:11:28,439
<i>I better keep stalling...</i>

181
00:11:30,566 --> 00:11:32,484
Misa's phone is on voice-mail.

182
00:11:33,068 --> 00:11:35,738
I left her a message to call us.

183
00:11:36,655 --> 00:11:38,073
What are we going to do, Ryuzaki?

184
00:11:39,283 --> 00:11:40,451
Well...

185
00:11:41,243 --> 00:11:45,539
If Matsuda dies, that would justify
the suspicion against Yotsuba.

186
00:11:48,083 --> 00:11:50,169
Let's just watch the situation
for a while.

187
00:11:52,254 --> 00:11:53,380
What shall we do?

188
00:11:53,505 --> 00:11:55,758
The question is whether
he heard us or not.

189
00:11:56,425 --> 00:11:59,303
There is a possibility.
We've got to kill him.

190
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:02,514
But did he really come to
pitch his client to us?

191
00:12:03,390 --> 00:12:05,059
Could he be a police officer?

192
00:12:05,809 --> 00:12:06,894
He can't be.

193
00:12:07,519 --> 00:12:10,606
The Japanese police have completely
withdrawn from the Kira case.

194
00:12:11,273 --> 00:12:13,275
It doesn't matter who he is.

195
00:12:14,276 --> 00:12:15,778
We have to kill him.

196
00:12:20,866 --> 00:12:24,370
It might be good to have her
as the face of our company.

197
00:12:26,288 --> 00:12:30,542
Right? Her shoot will finish soon,
so please wait a moment.

198
00:12:34,964 --> 00:12:36,465
I'm tired.

199
00:12:40,302 --> 00:12:42,263
A message from Light!

200
00:12:42,263 --> 00:12:43,097
CALL HISTORY LIGHT (KNIGHT)
1 VOICEMAIL MESSAGE

201
00:12:43,097 --> 00:12:44,848
He really worries about me if I'm late.

202
00:12:49,103 --> 00:12:50,187
Misa...

203
00:12:50,271 --> 00:12:52,982
<i>Light... Sorry I've been
working so much.</i>

204
00:12:53,065 --> 00:12:54,191
<i>I'll be finished soon.</i>

205
00:12:54,566 --> 00:12:57,194
Misa, you're not
with Matsuda, are you?

206
00:12:57,903 --> 00:13:00,948
He's horrible!
He just abandoned me here...

207
00:13:02,658 --> 00:13:04,785
Oh, I'm getting a call
on my work phone.

208
00:13:05,828 --> 00:13:06,996
It's from Matsu.

209
00:13:07,746 --> 00:13:09,373
Misa got a call from Matsuda.

210
00:13:10,207 --> 00:13:12,876
Tell Misa to let us listen in as well.

211
00:13:14,461 --> 00:13:18,382
<i>Misa-Misa, when you're finished with the shoot,
come to Y0tsuba's main Tokyo offices.</i>

212
00:13:18,882 --> 00:13:22,344
You may be able to appear
in Yotsuba's commercials.

213
00:13:22,678 --> 00:13:23,846
I'm negotiating with them right now.

214
00:13:24,388 --> 00:13:27,182
What? Really?
That's amazing, Matsu!

215
00:13:27,349 --> 00:13:28,851
So that's what you've been up to!

216
00:13:29,351 --> 00:13:31,145
<i>I'll do my best!</i>

217
00:13:31,437 --> 00:13:33,814
<i>Yeah. It's a short trip by taxi.</i>

218
00:13:37,026 --> 00:13:40,446
Light, we may be able to
save Matsuda.

219
00:13:41,322 --> 00:13:46,410
But we'll need Misa's help.
I'm sure she'll listen to you.

220
00:13:49,955 --> 00:13:51,206
I'm Misa-Misa!

221
00:13:51,540 --> 00:13:55,210
I don't do nudes,
but swimsuits and lingerie are okay!

222
00:13:56,086 --> 00:13:57,588
Pleased to meet you!

223
00:14:00,674 --> 00:14:03,969
She's really cute in person.

224
00:14:04,553 --> 00:14:07,097
That's not the problem right now,
don't you think?

225
00:14:07,556 --> 00:14:09,641
Matsu, since this is for Yotsuba,

226
00:14:09,725 --> 00:14:12,436
I got the okay from the offices
to have a special reception.

227
00:14:12,978 --> 00:14:14,355
Hm? Special?

228
00:14:15,606 --> 00:14:17,107
Good evening!

229
00:14:17,566 --> 00:14:19,526
Pleased to meet you!

230
00:14:20,194 --> 00:14:24,073
We'll be entertaining you with
all the girls from the agency tonight!

231
00:14:24,740 --> 00:14:27,576
Hey, don't you think this is
headed in a weird direction?

232
00:14:28,410 --> 00:14:29,495
It can't be helped.

233
00:14:30,579 --> 00:14:33,082
Right now, we can't leave
that manager alone.

234
00:14:34,124 --> 00:14:35,959
Since we're here,
I'm just going to enjoy myself.

235
00:14:43,092 --> 00:14:45,594
<i>Ryuzaki and the others
can see us from here.</i>

236
00:14:46,136 --> 00:14:47,179
<i>I might be saved...</i>

237
00:14:50,599 --> 00:14:51,934
Here! Please drink! Drink!

238
00:14:52,851 --> 00:14:54,228
<i>This is heaven.</i>

239
00:14:55,604 --> 00:14:57,981
Misa's pretty good at this.

240
00:15:05,072 --> 00:15:06,156
Now then...

241
00:15:08,534 --> 00:15:10,285
I'm going to the restroom.

242
00:15:20,170 --> 00:15:21,588
Ryuzaki, are you watching?

243
00:15:21,922 --> 00:15:23,006
Yes.

244
00:15:23,090 --> 00:15:24,174
<i>Umm, sorry, I...</i>

245
00:15:24,258 --> 00:15:26,051
Never mind that already.

246
00:15:26,260 --> 00:15:27,386
<i>Yes.</i>

247
00:15:27,636 --> 00:15:28,762
The eight who are here,
were having a meeting

248
00:15:28,846 --> 00:15:31,223
to determine
who they would get Kira to kill.

249
00:15:32,641 --> 00:15:35,769
I heard it clearly.
It's definitely them.

250
00:15:36,353 --> 00:15:37,646
It's probably true.

251
00:15:38,313 --> 00:15:42,401
But if you did overhear them,
then they should be trying to kill you.

252
00:15:43,777 --> 00:15:44,945
I figured that...

253
00:15:45,571 --> 00:15:47,322
ls there anything I can do?

254
00:15:48,157 --> 00:15:50,868
<i>Luckily, you're still alive,
so we may be able to save you.</i>

255
00:15:51,410 --> 00:15:52,453
<i>But for that to happen...</i>

256
00:15:53,078 --> 00:15:54,997
You must die before they kill you.

257
00:15:55,497 --> 00:15:56,498
What?

258
00:15:56,748 --> 00:15:58,792
I want you to listen to me very closely.

259
00:16:06,884 --> 00:16:08,010
You can't mean...

260
00:16:09,052 --> 00:16:10,971
That's impossible!

261
00:16:12,514 --> 00:16:13,891
Isn't that so?

262
00:16:13,974 --> 00:16:15,100
In other words...

263
00:16:15,184 --> 00:16:17,728
No, there are some exes
that I still think about.

264
00:16:18,020 --> 00:16:20,063
Our company is still expanding.

265
00:16:26,820 --> 00:16:27,905
What's going on?!

266
00:16:31,116 --> 00:16:34,244
Man...l am <i>s0</i> drunk.

267
00:16:35,662 --> 00:16:37,372
It feels good!

268
00:16:38,290 --> 00:16:41,251
Hey, is everyone having fun?

269
00:16:42,127 --> 00:16:44,588
That's no good.
You should be enjoying yourselves...

270
00:16:45,797 --> 00:16:48,175
Now, everyone...
The thing you've been waiting for!

271
00:16:48,258 --> 00:16:51,220
Showtime with Taro Matsui!

272
00:16:53,972 --> 00:16:55,641
Hey, what are you doing?

273
00:16:57,184 --> 00:16:59,478
Go, Mr. Matsui!

274
00:17:00,395 --> 00:17:01,438
Alley 00p...

275
00:17:05,651 --> 00:17:07,569
Hey, you're drunk!
That's dangerous.

276
00:17:08,028 --> 00:17:10,113
It's all right...

277
00:17:10,864 --> 00:17:12,533
I always do this.

278
00:17:18,747 --> 00:17:21,583
- Stop it! It's dangerous!
- You idiot!

279
00:17:21,833 --> 00:17:23,669
It's all right...

280
00:17:43,355 --> 00:17:44,398
He fell!

281
00:17:47,192 --> 00:17:48,277
This is bad...

282
00:17:48,694 --> 00:17:50,195
Oh no!

283
00:17:50,779 --> 00:17:53,448
I heard a thud so I came out,
how horrible!

284
00:17:53,657 --> 00:17:56,493
- Call emergency! Call Emergency!
- Man, fh/ls role sucks...

285
00:17:57,452 --> 00:18:00,914
Everyone, leave this to us and go home.

286
00:18:00,998 --> 00:18:02,207
What? But...

287
00:18:02,624 --> 00:18:05,877
It's all right. But please consider me
for the commercial.

288
00:18:06,253 --> 00:18:09,506
Hurry. It will be bad if
the press sees us here.

289
00:18:09,881 --> 00:18:10,882
Yeah.

290
00:18:14,636 --> 00:18:16,346
What's going on?!
Did someone jump?!

291
00:18:18,473 --> 00:18:21,351
Well, it's good that we saw him
die right before our eyes.

292
00:18:22,144 --> 00:18:23,186
Hey!

293
00:18:32,571 --> 00:18:37,159
I know we're shorthanded,
but I don't like doing this.

294
00:18:38,577 --> 00:18:40,203
Matsuda, you idiot.

295
00:18:55,719 --> 00:18:58,847
Misa Amane's manager dies...

296
00:18:58,847 --> 00:18:59,389
ENTERTAINER MISA AMANE'S MANAGER
DIES IN DRUNKEN FALL.

297
00:19:03,560 --> 00:19:05,771
UNKNOWN NUMBER

298
00:19:05,979 --> 00:19:06,980
Yes?

299
00:19:07,230 --> 00:19:09,191
<i>You're Masahiko Kida, V. P. of
the Rights and Planning Department...</i>

300
00:19:09,274 --> 00:19:12,569
<i>at the Yotsuba Group's main
Tokyo branch, aren't you?</i>

301
00:19:13,278 --> 00:19:15,614
Yes, that's right.
Who are you?

302
00:19:16,448 --> 00:19:20,786
My name is Eraldo Coil.
I'd like to discuss my terms with you.

303
00:19:22,537 --> 00:19:26,375
A $2 million advance and
$8 million upon completion?

304
00:19:26,667 --> 00:19:27,709
Are you out of your mind?

305
00:19:28,251 --> 00:19:30,212
And even if we don't
commission him,

306
00:19:30,295 --> 00:19:32,589
we have to pay him $2 million
to keep him silent.

307
00:19:33,799 --> 00:19:34,883
Hush money, huh?

308
00:19:35,884 --> 00:19:39,262
We should assume that
Coil knows quite a bit already.

309
00:19:40,722 --> 00:19:44,768
That's pretty bad.
I want out of these meetings!

310
00:19:45,644 --> 00:19:47,312
I don't know who Kira is,

311
00:19:47,396 --> 00:19:50,232
but I don't want to get wrapped up
in this and get myself arrested!

312
00:19:52,734 --> 00:19:53,735
Hatori...

313
00:19:54,778 --> 00:19:57,572
You're going to be dead tomorrow.

314
00:20:04,663 --> 00:20:06,707
Wait! I was just joking!

315
00:20:08,875 --> 00:20:10,711
I'll do it.
I'll stay and do it!

316
00:20:11,169 --> 00:20:12,295
So what are we going to do?

317
00:20:12,921 --> 00:20:16,091
Coil is willing to accept ourjob
despite what he knows.

318
00:20:16,675 --> 00:20:18,552
He'll become partners
with us as long as we pay him.

319
00:20:18,927 --> 00:20:19,928
That's what it means.

320
00:20:20,512 --> 00:20:24,141
We need to have someone
as skilled as Coil on our side.

321
00:20:24,599 --> 00:20:25,851
That's right. Pay him.

322
00:20:25,934 --> 00:20:27,269
It doesn't matter how much it'll cost.

323
00:20:28,061 --> 00:20:29,604
That's right, pay him!

324
00:20:41,408 --> 00:20:43,493
All right, we'll contract Coil.

325
00:20:44,077 --> 00:20:45,162
Any objections?

326
00:20:45,454 --> 00:20:46,455
No objections.

327
00:20:49,458 --> 00:20:50,667
L, are you listening?

328
00:20:51,460 --> 00:20:55,464
I'm so disappointed.
The security level here is horrible.

329
00:20:56,256 --> 00:20:58,425
They only have a contract
with a security company.

330
00:20:58,967 --> 00:21:00,761
There weren't even any
wiretap detectors.

331
00:21:02,095 --> 00:21:04,931
It's been one week since I snuck in.

332
00:21:05,265 --> 00:21:08,101
Things seem to be
moving very smoothly.

333
00:21:08,685 --> 00:21:09,728
We're almost there.

334
00:21:10,312 --> 00:21:12,481
One of them...

335
00:21:14,775 --> 00:21:15,817
is Kira.

336
00:21:16,443 --> 00:21:18,987
<i>Now then,
let's commence our regular meeting.</i>

337
00:21:19,446 --> 00:21:22,324
There only appears to be
seven of them instead of eight.

338
00:21:22,783 --> 00:21:25,827
TO BE CONTINUED

339
00:21:26,203 --> 00:21:31,374
<i>I dreamed a dream
that no one could see,</i>

340
00:21:31,458 --> 00:21:36,755
<i>I threw away everything
that I didn't need</i>

341
00:21:37,130 --> 00:21:40,467
<i>I'm holding these feelings</i>

342
00:21:40,550 --> 00:21:45,764
<i>That I can't give up in my heart</i>

343
00:21:45,889 --> 00:21:52,145
<i>Even if my feet fall victim
to the shackles of sacrifice</i>

344
00:21:52,229 --> 00:21:57,442
<i>In between reality and my ideal</i>

345
00:21:57,526 --> 00:22:02,405
<i>I can't hold back
the flooding impulses</i>

346
00:22:02,739 --> 00:22:06,326
<i>Because I have a strong desire</i>

347
00:22:06,409 --> 00:22:09,871
<i>To accomplish</i>

348
00:22:10,497 --> 00:22:15,085
<i>[deceit] [fear] [vanity] [melancholy]</i>

349
00:22:15,502 --> 00:22:20,632
<i>I'm not weak enough to believe</i>

350
00:22:20,715 --> 00:22:25,846
<i>Any of these negative perceptions</i>

351
00:22:26,304 --> 00:22:31,685
<i>I'm a trickster
who doesn't know solitude</i>

352
00:22:35,814 --> 00:22:37,440
PREVIEW

353
00:22:37,440 --> 00:22:38,483
Ryuzaki!

354
00:22:38,859 --> 00:22:42,237
Even after I catch
the current Kira...

355
00:22:42,612 --> 00:22:45,490
do you think that I could
become Kira, a murderer?

356
00:22:46,199 --> 00:22:48,118
Do I look like that kind of person?

357
00:22:48,118 --> 00:22:50,829
NEXT EPISODE: MAKESHIFT

